A federal judge has sentenced former Blackwater security guard Nicholas Slatten to life in prison for his role in a 2007 shooting that killed 14 Iraqi civilians and wounded 17 others .
Three other guards - Paul Slough , Evan Liberty and Dustin Heard were each sentenced to 30 years and one day in prison after charges that included manslaughter , attempted manslaughter and using firearms while committing a felony .
